name: Dökk [Gadget-2 | Cluster simulation #1]
description: Created by @fuse_works on 15 June 2017 during the prototyping phase of Dökk live-media performance. The simulation operated on the servers for almost a week, generating 500 snapshots of the state of matter in a uniform universe made up of 276,498 particles. These elements represent the contribution to the formation of a velocity vector field, the final result of the study, represented by a cube of which each side is 100 million light years in length. 2160 ×2160px PNG
